00:05:31.276 --> 00:05:34.526
one basketball costs one pair of shoes,

00:05:35.664 --> 00:05:39.831
so a basketball here in country
B costs one pair of shoes,

00:05:41.463 --> 00:05:45.807
so one pair of shoes, S once
again is a pair of shoes

00:05:45.807 --> 00:05:47.601
and you could have also gotten it

00:05:47.601 --> 00:05:49.465
from this information here,

00:05:49.465 --> 00:05:52.732
you could set up an
equation, you could say look,

00:05:52.732 --> 00:05:56.036
if I put all of, in country A, if I put,

00:05:56.036 --> 00:05:59.405
so let's look at this
part right over here,

00:05:59.405 --> 00:06:02.816
you could say in country A,
if I put all of my energy

00:06:02.816 --> 00:06:05.918
into basketballs, I could
produce eight basketballs,

00:06:05.918 --> 00:06:08.588
but if I put that same energy into shoes,

00:06:08.588 --> 00:06:11.871
I could produce six pairs of shoes,

00:06:11.871 --> 00:06:14.685
so with the same energy, I could
produce either one of these

00:06:14.685 --> 00:06:17.310
and then if I want the
opportunity costs for basketballs,

00:06:17.310 --> 00:06:19.021
I divide both by eight
and that's essentially

00:06:19.021 --> 00:06:22.688
what I did over here
and I get a basketball,

00:06:23.951 --> 00:06:26.829
it costs six eighths of a pair of shoes

00:06:26.829 --> 00:06:28.830
or three fourths of a pair of shoes,

00:06:28.830 --> 00:06:31.987
which is exactly what I have over here.

00:06:31.987 --> 00:06:33.582
Now let's do the opportunity cost

00:06:33.582 --> 00:06:36.001
for a pair of shoes in either country,

00:06:36.001 --> 00:06:38.039
well, there's a couple of
ways to think about it,

00:06:38.039 --> 00:06:39.960
you could just view it as the reciprocal

00:06:39.960 --> 00:06:43.834
or you could even go back to
this equation right over here,

00:06:43.834 --> 00:06:48.523
if we are in country A,
we would say six shoes,

00:06:48.523 --> 00:06:49.710
if we put all our energy in shoes,

00:06:49.710 --> 00:06:51.794
we could produce six of them

00:06:51.794 --> 00:06:53.521
or six pairs of shoes, I should say

00:06:53.521 --> 00:06:55.841
and if we put all of our
energy into basketballs,

00:06:55.841 --> 00:06:58.308
we could produce eight basketballs,

00:06:58.308 --> 00:07:02.871
but if you divide by six,
you get per pair of shoes

00:07:02.871 --> 00:07:05.157
and so per each pair of shoes,

00:07:05.157 --> 00:07:08.750
the energy to produce one
pair of shoes is equivalent

00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:12.065
to the energy to produce
eight sixths of a basketball

00:07:12.065 --> 00:07:14.494
and eight sixths is the same thing

00:07:14.494 --> 00:07:16.986
as four thirds of a basketball

00:07:16.986 --> 00:07:19.200
and if we wanted to write it as a decimal

00:07:19.200 --> 00:07:21.818
just for simplicity or maybe
to make it easier to compare,

00:07:21.818 --> 00:07:24.669
we would say that this
is approximately 1.33,

00:07:24.669 --> 00:07:27.524
obviously the 3s just keep
going on, it repeats forever,

00:07:27.524 --> 00:07:30.998
but approximately 1.33 basketballs

00:07:30.998 --> 00:07:32.532
is the cost of producing a shoe

00:07:32.532 --> 00:07:34.800
and the opportunity
cost of producing a shoe

00:07:34.800 --> 00:07:37.300
in country A, 1.33 basketballs

00:07:38.945 --> 00:07:41.077
and what about in country B?

00:07:41.077 --> 00:07:42.353
Well, in country B

00:07:42.353 --> 00:07:44.883
we could set up a
similar type of equation,

00:07:44.883 --> 00:07:47.366
where the same energy for four shoes,

00:07:47.366 --> 00:07:49.281
I could produce four basketballs

00:07:49.281 --> 00:07:50.645
and that's essentially what we set up

00:07:50.645 --> 00:07:53.672
right over here on the left,
you divide both sides by four,

00:07:53.672 --> 00:07:56.956
the energy of a shoe is equal
to the energy of a basketball,

00:07:56.956 --> 00:07:59.298
or I should say the
energy of a pair of shoes

00:07:59.298 --> 00:08:01.802
is equal to the energy
of making a basketball,

00:08:01.802 --> 00:08:05.037
so the opportunity cost
of making a pair of shoes

00:08:05.037 --> 00:08:07.287
is equal to one basketball.

00:08:08.455 --> 00:08:11.582
So now we're ready to draw the connection,

00:08:11.582 --> 00:08:14.872
given the opportunity
costs that we calculated,

00:08:14.872 --> 00:08:19.039
what country has the comparative
advantage in basketballs?

