Pause this video and try to figure it out.

00:08:21.703 --> 00:08:23.677
So now let's look at the opportunity cost

00:08:23.677 --> 00:08:26.543
of producing a basketball
in either country.

00:08:26.543 --> 00:08:30.951
In country A, each
basketball costs a worker

00:08:30.951 --> 00:08:32.642
three fourths of a pair of shoes,

00:08:32.642 --> 00:08:36.897
while in country B, it costs
them a whole pair of shoes,

00:08:36.897 --> 00:08:40.893
so country A actually has
a lower opportunity cost

00:08:40.893 --> 00:08:42.875
of producing basketballs

00:08:42.875 --> 00:08:45.829
and so it has the
comparative advantage here,

00:08:45.829 --> 00:08:48.662
comparative, comparative advantage

00:08:51.192 --> 00:08:55.558
and then if we look at shoes,
it goes the other way around,

00:08:55.558 --> 00:08:57.694
country A has an opportunity cost

00:08:57.694 --> 00:09:01.590
of one and one third basketballs
for every pair of shoes,

00:09:01.590 --> 00:09:03.624
while country B has an opportunity cost

00:09:03.624 --> 00:09:05.928
of only one basketball per pair of shoes,

00:09:05.928 --> 00:09:08.767
so it has a lower opportunity cost

00:09:08.767 --> 00:09:10.514
and this one actually might be

00:09:10.514 --> 00:09:12.467
a little bit counterintuitive,

00:09:12.467 --> 00:09:15.875
because if you look on the
shoe axis right over here,

00:09:15.875 --> 00:09:20.348
country A has the absolute
advantage in producing shoes,

00:09:20.348 --> 00:09:22.416
a worker per day in country A

00:09:22.416 --> 00:09:24.470
can produce six pairs of shoes,

00:09:24.470 --> 00:09:25.845
while a worker in country B

00:09:25.845 --> 00:09:28.494
can only produce four pairs of shoes,

00:09:28.494 --> 00:09:31.576
but even though country A
has the absolute advantage,

00:09:31.576 --> 00:09:33.924
it would actually make sense for country A

00:09:33.924 --> 00:09:38.592
to focus on basketballs, while
country B focuses on shoes

00:09:38.592 --> 00:09:41.570
and in the next video,
we'll see how they can

00:09:41.570 --> 00:09:43.880
trade with each other
to get to a scenario,

00:09:43.880 --> 00:09:47.300
that is beyond their
production possibility curves

00:09:47.300 --> 00:09:49.754
and why focusing on your
comparative advantage,

00:09:49.754 --> 00:09:51.304
at least in this theoretical,

00:09:51.304 --> 00:09:54.221
very simplified world, makes sense.

